29/10/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- Defence Minister Evangelos Meimarakis met with Turkish counterpart Vecdi Gonul on Tuesday (October 28th) in Thessaloniki.
They discussed ways to boost co-operation in the defence sector and in fighting natural disasters.
They also reportedly focused on a programme for joint production of F-16 fighter jets.
Turkey will implement it with the participation of the Greek aerospace industry.
Later, the two ministers attended an annual military parade commemorating Greece's entry into World War II on October 28th 1940.
(Anadolu news agency, ANA-MPA - 28/10/08)
